<subSubSection id="FFD721D2FFF37213FF3DF1A8FDF8FD6A" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B7727259FFF37213FF3DF1A8FDF8FD6A" blockId="10.[151,1436,151,371]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="85B9AE4BFFF37213FF3DF1A8FE28FCA8" bold="true" box="[198,410,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
. For inflorescence bracts and proximal flower pit shape, 
<taxonomicName id="70CD09DAFFF37213FBB1F1A7FA2EFCA8" authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="2012" box="[1098,1436,152,177]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Pholidostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amazonensis">
<emphasis id="85B9AE4BFFF37213FBB1F1A7FA2EFCA8" box="[1098,1436,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pholidostachys amazonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the same character states as 
<taxonomicName id="70CD09DAFFF37213FDAEF180FD4DFCC1" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Martius" box="[597,767,191,216]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Pholidostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="synanthera">
<emphasis id="85B9AE4BFFF37213FDAEF180FD4DFCC1" box="[597,767,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. synanthera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Fruits are lacking on the single specimen available. However, inflorescences of the two are quite different. 
<taxonomicName id="70CD09DAFFF37213FCE3F1DAFBDAFCE7" authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="2012" box="[792,1128,229,254]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Pholidostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amazonensis">
<emphasis id="85B9AE4BFFF37213FCE3F1DAFBDAFCE7" box="[792,1128,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pholidostachys amazonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has spicate inflorescences with a well-developed peduncle, absent rachis, and 1 rachilla, this arching at anthesis. 
<taxonomicName id="70CD09DAFFF37213FB25F033FEA9FD52" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Martius" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Pholidostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="synanthera">
<emphasis id="85B9AE4BFFF37213FB25F033FEA9FD52" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pholidostachys synanthera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has inflorescences branched 1–2 orders with a well-developed peduncle and rachis, and several rachillae, these spreading at anthesis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
